==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Germane
<hw>Ger*mane"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>German</er>
akin, nearly related.]</ety> <def>Literally, near akin; hence, closely
allied; appropriate or fitting; relevant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The phrase would be more <qex>germane</qex> to the matter.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[An amendment] must be <qex>germane</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Barclay
(Digest).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Germanic</ent>⟦br⟧
